          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "LSTM_y_pred = LSTM_model.predict(X_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bMxNjlEollLM"
      },
      "source": [
        "#Results\n",
        "* Invert the Robust Scaling on the actual values and predicting vaules\n",
        "* Mae:  the average of the absolute differences between predictions and actual values.\n",
        "* R2 Score: the proportion of the variance in the dependent variable that is predictable from the independent variable(s). A higher R2 score indicates a better fit of the model to the data.\n",
        "* MAPE: It's a measure of the accuracy of a forecasting method. It expresses the accuracy as a percentage of the error relative to the actual value."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
